<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="163" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="64.[806,1422,591,1103]" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">
<emphasis box="[806,925,592,613]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Species similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="VOCKEROTH" authorityYear="1969" box="[1194,1358,591,613]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornutum">
<emphasis box="[1194,1358,591,613]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">C. bicornutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" box="[806,982,622,643]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asombrosum">
<emphasis box="[806,982,622,643]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">C. asombrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with black facial vitta and costal cell microtrichose. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="VOCKEROTH" authorityYear="1969" box="[991,1325,653,674]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sedlacekorum">
<emphasis box="[991,1325,653,674]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">Citrogramma sedlacekorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the others two species by male frontal triangle with a medial triangular dark macula, lunule black (
<figureCitation box="[814,947,744,767]" captionStart="Figures 3–14" captionStartId="13.[164,254,1643,1662]" captionTargetBox="[324,1280,200,1608]" captionTargetId="figure-0@13.[319,1287,194,1614]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 3–14. 3, Citrogramma amarilla, frontal view of female head. 4, Citrogramma flavigenum, frontal view of male head. 5–7, Citrogramma bicornutum: 5, frontal view of male head; 6, dorsal view of male head; 7, anterodorsal view of female head. 8–10, Citrogramma pennardsi: 8, dorsal view of male abdomen; 9, dorsal view of male head; 10, ventral view of male genitalia (detail). 11–14, Citrogramma sedlacekorum: 11, dorsal view of female abdomen; 12, dorsal view of male head; 13, dorsal view of female head; 14, dorsal view of male abdomen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406159/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">Figs 12, 13</figureCitation>
), scutellum yellow with a medial dark macula reaching anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1356,775,797]" captionStart="Figures 3–14" captionStartId="13.[164,254,1643,1662]" captionTargetBox="[324,1280,200,1608]" captionTargetId="figure-0@13.[319,1287,194,1614]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 3–14. 3, Citrogramma amarilla, frontal view of female head. 4, Citrogramma flavigenum, frontal view of male head. 5–7, Citrogramma bicornutum: 5, frontal view of male head; 6, dorsal view of male head; 7, anterodorsal view of female head. 8–10, Citrogramma pennardsi: 8, dorsal view of male abdomen; 9, dorsal view of male head; 10, ventral view of male genitalia (detail). 11–14, Citrogramma sedlacekorum: 11, dorsal view of female abdomen; 12, dorsal view of male head; 13, dorsal view of female head; 14, dorsal view of male abdomen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406159/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">Figs 11, 14</figureCitation>
) and anal lobe bare basally. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="VOCKEROTH" authorityYear="1969" box="[1097,1421,806,827]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sedlacekorum">
<emphasis box="[1097,1421,806,827]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">Citrogramma sedlacekorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has enlarged male genitalia, very singular, with sternum 8 presenting three subcylindrical processes (
<figureCitation box="[814,909,897,919]" captionStart="Figures 154–157" captionStartId="28.[144,234,1518,1537]" captionTargetBox="[308,1263,205,1479]" captionTargetId="figure-112@28.[299,1267,195,1488]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figures 154–157. Male genitalia. 154, Citrogramma sedlacekorum (from Vockeroth, 1969): a, left lateral view (sternum 8 included); b, superior lobe, lateral, outline only; c, sternum 9, superior lobes and aedeagal base, ventral view; d, right surstylus, lateral view. 155, Citrogramma pintada, left lateral view. 156, Citrogramma pinyton, left lateral view. 157, Citrogramma notiale: a, left lateral view; b, superior lobe, lateral, outline only; c, sternum 9, superior lobes and aedeagal base, ventral view; d, right surstylus, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406189/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="163">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
